# Cloudflare Pages headers configuration.
#
# Why this file exists:
# A facilitator who redeploys this app between sessions can otherwise serve
# stale HTML / JS to anyone whose browser cached the previous build. The
# symptom is exactly the failure mode we hit during early testing: students
# see an old version of the UI even after a successful redeploy.
#
# `Cache-Control: no-cache` tells the browser to revalidate every request
# with the server before reusing a cached response. The server (Cloudflare)
# answers with a 304 Not Modified when the file is unchanged, so the actual
# transferred bytes are tiny. The cost is one round-trip per file per page
# load, which is negligible for a classroom app and well worth the
# guarantee that a redeploy is picked up immediately.

/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache
